        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Is Fe³⁺ Consistently More Stable? — **Yes, without exception.**\n\nAcross all 40 ligands with retrievable paired log β values near 25 °C, **Fe³⁺ is more stable in every single case**. The advantage spans from a tiny ~0.1 log units for soft halides to over 20 log units for purpose-built siderophores:\n\n| Ligand | log β (Fe³⁺) | log β (Fe²⁺) | Δlog β |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Desferrioxamine B | 30.60 | 10.00 | **+20.6** |\n| TTHA | 35.20 | 22.10 | +13.1 |\n| 2,3-Dihydroxybenzoate | 21.50 | 7.40 | +14.1 |\n| Catecholate | 20.01 | 7.80 | +12.2 |\n| Tiron | 20.40 | 7.60 | +12.8 |\n| CDTA | 27.40 | 16.20 | +11.2 |\n| Salicylate | 16.35 | 5.20 | +11.2 |\n| DTPA | 28.60 | 16.50 | +12.1 |\n| EDTA | 25.10 | 14.32 | +10.8 |\n| Acetohydroxamate | 11.40 | 4.20 | +7.2 |\n| Citrate | 11.50 | 4.40 | +7.1 |\n| Tartrate | 7.49 | 2.06 | +5.4 |\n| Glycine | 10.01 | 4.31 | +5.7 |\n| Oxalate | 9.40 | 4.72 | +4.7 |\n| Fluoride | 5.28 | 0.97 | +4.3 |\n| Hydroxide | 11.81 | 4.60 | +7.2 |\n| Phosphate | 9.35 | 3.20 | +6.2 |\n| Pyrophosphate | 22.78 | 5.60 | +17.2 |\n| 1,10-Phenanthroline | 6.50 | 5.85 | +0.7 |\n| 2,2′-Bipyridine | 5.80 | 4.20 | +1.6 |\n| Thiocyanate | 2.95 | 1.18 | +1.8 |\n| Iodide | 0.20 | 0.10 | +0.1 |",
